message: The Frederick Douglass Trafficking Victims Prevention and Protection Reauthorization Act of 2017 has bipartisan congressional support and bolsters trafficker prosecution. The anti-trafficking legislation authorizes funding for programs revolving around four aspects: preventing trafficking, protecting victims, prosecuting traffickers and their clients, and partnering with organizations active at the local level.
